./sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260416T054258Z_1776366099.log:161:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-16T19:02:15.940Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776366135940_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-019@20260416T054258Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini-3-flash-preview\n**Date:** 2026-04-16\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis_architecture_registry.py`\n- `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py`\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation accurately fulfills all acceptance criteria. The registry in `synthesis_architecture_registry.py` defines the six required synthesis architectures (subtractive, FM, additive, granular, physical modeling, and spectral/FFT). Each entry includes:\n- `role_tags` for production role affinity.\n- `macro_controls` with `SafeRange` definitions (default, min, max).\n- `arc_affinity` mapping to the five required arc phases (Divination, Emergence, Conversation, Convergence, Crystallization).\n- `fallback` strategies for robust resolution.\n\n## Completeness\nThe solution is complete. It covers all synthesis families and provides helper functions (`strategies_for_role`, `best_architecture_for_phase`, `resolve_architecture`) that allow the score tree and tracker scenes to request architectures by production role or arc phase. The integration points in `music_tracker.py` via `_PRODUCTION_COURSE_METADATA_KEYS` ensure that these strategies are available to the tracker.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established patterns in the `senseweave` directory, utilizing dataclasses and typed literals. It maintains consistency with `procedural_arc.py` and `production_course.py`, as verified by the integration tests.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices were identified. The use of `SafeRange` for parameter bounds provides a layer of safety for synthesis parameters.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured, clearly documented, and accompanied by a comprehensive test suite. The tests (`tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry.py`) pass successfully and cover registry completeness, field validation, affinity logic, and consistency with other modules.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and well-tested. The choice of `frozenset` for REQUIRED_* constants and the use of `ArchitectureId.__args__` for reflection are elegant touches that keep the registry maintainable.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-019@20260416t054258z-verify.md"}}
