CHANGELOG.md:178:- Added depth-2 sample-status end-to-end test coverage (frac-0112): `tests/test_sample_status.py` now includes `SampleStatusEndToEndTests`, which drives `senseweave.sample_status.sample_status_text` and `face_display_sample_status_text` through one realistic face-display / operator lifecycle: legacy mode where playback dominates renders a `playing self bus · freeze bed` line, legacy mode where capture is the only active sub-system renders `sampling theramini in via room mic · grain cloud`, combined mode joins `currently sampling theramini in via room mic` with `playing sample freeze bed from source self bus` via ` · `, a `no_capture` monitor failure prefixes the combined output with `monitor offline`, the `face_display_sample_status_text` wrapper agrees with the combined-mode call (with and without monitor failure), and a primitive diagnostic of the rendered lines round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sample_status_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `senseweave.sample_status` already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4661 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:248:- Added depth-2 governor integration end-to-end test coverage (frac-0081): `tests/test_governor_integration.py` now includes `TestGovernorIntegrationEndToEnd` which drives the resource governor lifecycle through nominal, emergency spike, recovery, CPU-only, and master-bus-dead paths. `tests/test_governor_integration_depth.py` pins the file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:286:- Added depth-2 capstone-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0062): `tests/test_capstone_engine.py` now includes `TestCapstoneCycleEndToEnd`, which drives the existing public `build_capstone_cycle()` API through complete EMSD capstone planning paths. The new tests verify all five canonical phases expose linked family, patch, arc, palette, mix, sampling, and DSP contracts; assert occupied Theramini routing activates the Conversation dialogue path and ducking behavior; assert away-practice late phases retarget sampling and DSP focus to `self_bus`; compare quiet cadences against occupied cycles for lower density and quieter mix targets; verify repertoire songs shape identity families, patches, imagery, and statement text; and round-trip phase diagnostics through `json.dumps`. `tests/test_capstone_engine_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 9 real functions versus 2 trivial). Existing capstone assertions and `my-claw/tools/senseweave/capstone_engine.py` source behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4401 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:456:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:459:- Closed the server-side gap on the new master-bus sampler controls: added a `master_smooth.scd` SuperCollider source stub for `sw_master_smooth` that declares `sampler_amp` and `sampler_bypass_comp` (both default 1.0) alongside the existing `amp` / `drive` / `warmth` / `reverb` / `room` surface; refactored `start_audio.sh` and `restart_composer.sh` to seed the master node via `senseweave.master_bus.master_bus_s_new_args()` so the boot-time `/s_new sw_master_smooth` arg list stays in lockstep with `DEFAULT_MASTER_BUS_VALUES`; added `tests/test_master_smooth_scd.py` to pin the stub's control declarations and the boot scripts' helper-driven seeding.
CHANGELOG.md:468:- Added SuperCollider recipe references for curriculum: created 22 discoverable recipe files in `my-claw/curriculum/recipes/supercollider/` for topics from MIDI-to-frequency to master-bus, linked them from EMSD-102 and EMSD-130 reference docs, and added static validation tests in `tests/test_supercollider_recipes.py` that check for required labels without coupling to the live audio server.
CHANGELOG.md:489:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
CHANGELOG.md:490:- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
CHANGELOG.md:492:- Fixed the live score-tree runtime on CypherClaw: `duet_composer.py` now derives commission context defensively from the world when `TrackerPlan` lacks `day_phase` / `weekly_phase`, `master_bus.py` now exposes an explicit `sw_master_smooth` seed helper, and `restart_composer.sh` now reseeds that master node again after the new composer PID is confirmed alive so the first piece does not run with scene-level `/n_set` traffic targeting a dead node.
CHANGELOG.md:496:- Hardened the slow observer-vision path: `observer_vision.py` now treats Ollama `503 server busy / maximum pending requests exceeded` as queue saturation instead of a user-facing description, preserves the HTTP body detail in `vision_error`, emits a compact local fallback description with `vision_backend: \"local_fallback\"`, and backs off before retrying the multimodal model call again.
CHANGELOG.md:504:- Added real EMSD master-bus control: `master_bus.py` now translates live `mix_*` fields plus tracker-scene `master_amp` / `reverb_send` automation into `sw_master_smooth` `/n_set` updates at scene start, so EMSD mix intent now shapes the summed output path instead of only per-note rendering.
CHANGELOG.md:510:- Made the Scarlett recovery path deterministic: when real JACK needs to be rebuilt, `start_audio.sh` now clears stale JACK state, relaunches `jackdbus`, and configures the ALSA backend for `hw:USB` before starting `scsynth`, so the box can recover onto the Scarlett monitor path instead of drifting into a PipeWire-only fallback.
CHANGELOG.md:526:- Rebalanced EMSD source authority toward the room in lived-in late phases: capstone `Convergence` and `Crystallization` now prefer `room_mic` outside `away_practice`, DSP scene focus follows that same room bias, and `sample_dsp_activity.py` can retarget a sparse late-phase `self_bus` request onto a fresh room capture while still preserving the original requested source in state for operator visibility.
CHANGELOG.md:527:- Fixed room-capture triggering so external sample sources no longer depend on `self_listener` RMS. `room_mic`, `contact_mic`, and `theramini_in` now trigger from their own live cues, while only `self_bus` remains gated by self-audio level.
CHANGELOG.md:575:- Added SenseWeave operator diagnostics to daemon `/status`, including score tree, section function, arrangement curve, ear metrics, sample source, master bus, self-listener, and independent rollout flags for curriculum/exercise, preview render, self-critique, and long-form suites.
