my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:97:| CCS-009 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:99:| CCS-011 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:102:| CCS-014 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | MUST | T1 | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:114:| CCS-026 | Add per-mode effects-bus presets: solitary/evening favor more reverb + delay; working_ambience uses minimal effects; storm uses high freeze + heavy comb-B. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE: dict[str, dict]` mapping mode name to fx args<br/>- solitary: `delay_time=0.6, delay_feedback=0.65, verb_mix=0.45, freeze_amount=0.2, comb_b_amount=0.4`<br/>- companion: `delay_time=0.5, delay_feedback=0.4, verb_mix=0.3, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.15`<br/>- working_ambience: `delay_time=0.3, delay_feedback=0.2, verb_mix=0.15, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.1`<br/>- evening_reflection: `delay_time=0.7, delay_feedback=0.55, verb_mix=0.5, freeze_amount=0.15, comb_b_amount=0.3`<br/>- storm: `delay_time=0.25, delay_feedback=0.7, verb_mix=0.25, freeze_amount=0.55, comb_b_amount=0.6`<br/>- tests verify each preset, that values are within SynthDef-acceptable ranges, and that `dispatch_sample` correctly applies the preset for the active mode |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:121:| CCS-033 | Update `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to reflect the quintet, document the sampler architecture in `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md`, and add a one-page artistic-intent doc `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`. | MUST | T2 | - musicianship roadmap mentions the quintet and sampler-as-memory<br/>- architecture doc covers the data model, daemon, dispatch, effects bus, and selector<br/>- artistic-intent doc captures the three usages (memory of place, self-quotation, found library) and the five principles<br/>- docs link from each other; mkdocs / repo nav updated if applicable |
my-claw/sdp/prd-web-platform.md:65:| WEB-009 | Implement the WebSocket hub. Central event bus that broadcasts to all connected clients: (a) `vitals` — server metrics every 5s from I/O watchdog/Redis, (b) `chat` — new messages and agent responses, (c) `agent` — agent start/stop/output stream events, (d) `pipeline` — task status changes, (e) `pet` — state changes, XP gains, level-ups, (f) `art` — new artwork generated, (g) `alert` — warnings, I/O guard triggers, errors. Clients subscribe to channels. Server-side fan-out. Handle reconnection gracefully with missed-event replay from Redis. | MUST | T2 | - WebSocket hub broadcasts 7 event types<br/>- Clients receive events in real-time<br/>- Reconnection replays missed events from Redis<br/>- Multiple simultaneous clients supported<br/>- Events logged with timestamps<br/>- Backpressure handling for slow clients |
